{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDYyOTY4ODc3", "number": 6739, "title": "Exposes an argument in the mitochondria WDL", "bodyText": "@ahaessly Could you please take a look at this? We had a request to change this argument which wasn't previously possible since it was hardcoded into the WDL task. Ideally I'd like to expose all of the arguments but even wiring this one through the imported WDL was annoying. I tried making it an input to the task with a value like this:\ntask M2 {\n  input {\n    Int max_reads_arg = 75\n  }\n...\n\nwhich looks a lot cleaner (don't have to make sure you wire it through from the main inputs), but when I looked in Terra it didn't actually expose the argument (I'm assuming because the M2 task is in a sub-workflow). Any thoughts on how to make this better so I can expose everything? Or is this the best way to do that at the moment?", "createdAt": "2020-08-04T19:38:34Z", "url": "https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/pull/6739", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "356a9ddb50f1467717e87ee6c5ef1c2f084694d3"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-08-13T15:52:55Z", "author": {"login": "meganshand"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 6, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABc7r2BIAH2gAyNDYyOTY4ODc3Ojg1NWE3OTczZmNkZjg2NDA3YTMwMWZjYzBhNDZjM2U3MTE5MzM1NDY=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABc-hLB1AFqTQ2NjgzNTc2OA==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "855a7973fcdf86407a301fcc0a46c3e711933546", "author": {"user": {"login": "meganshand", "name": null}}, "url": "https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/commit/855a7973fcdf86407a301fcc0a46c3e711933546", "committedDate": "2020-08-04T19:32:32Z", "message": "exposing an argument"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "54becee730e56b6fea2818d0cc83dfb9fc0c2bed", "author": {"user": {"login": "ahaessly", "name": "Andrea Haessly"}}, "url": "https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/commit/54becee730e56b6fea2818d0cc83dfb9fc0c2bed", "committedDate": "2020-08-05T16:09:40Z", "message": "add allowNestedInputs param"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NDY0NDkzNjU3", "url": "https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/pull/6739#pullrequestreview-464493657", "createdAt": "2020-08-10T19:00:14Z", "commit": {"oid": "54becee730e56b6fea2818d0cc83dfb9fc0c2bed"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wOC0xMFQxOTowMDoxNVrOG-bZoQ==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wOC0xMFQxOTowMDoxNVrOG-bZoQ==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ2ODExMzgyNQ==", "bodyText": "Is there a reason why you don't initialize this in the input section instead of making this optional? e.g.,\ninput {\n   ...\n   Int max_reads_per_alignment_start = 75\n   ...\n}\n\nThis lets a caller override it but since it's not optional you don't need to select_first() on it.", "url": "https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/pull/6739#discussion_r468113825", "createdAt": "2020-08-10T19:00:15Z", "author": {"login": "pshapiro4broad"}, "path": "scripts/mitochondria_m2_wdl/AlignAndCall.wdl", "diffHunk": "@@ -462,6 +463,7 @@ task M2 {\n     Int? preemptible_tries\n   }\n \n+  Int max_reads_per_alignment_start_arg = select_first([max_reads_per_alignment_start, 75])", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "54becee730e56b6fea2818d0cc83dfb9fc0c2bed"}, "originalPosition": 12}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "bbe457eaab0489c4e94d1443ce12d05539ec2590", "author": {"user": {"login": "ahaessly", "name": "Andrea Haessly"}}, "url": "https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/commit/bbe457eaab0489c4e94d1443ce12d05539ec2590", "committedDate": "2020-08-13T14:36:30Z", "message": "use default assignment instead of optional"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "a28b415ca71f05e